Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.03,0:00:04.34,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Titanic had enough\Nlifeboats to satisfy the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.34,0:00:05.65,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,law.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.43,0:00:07.71,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,That sentence sounds\Nsafe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.57,0:00:11.34,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,In 1912, it was the\Nproblem.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.62,0:00:15.00,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,British rules measured\Nlifeboats by tonnage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.88,0:00:18.93,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Above 10,000 tons, the\Ntop bracket required
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.93,0:00:21.99,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,16 lifeboats for 990\Npeople.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.89,0:00:26.19,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Titanic carried 16\Nlifeboats and four
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.19,0:00:29.50,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,collapsibles, enough\Nfor about 1,176 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.40,0:00:33.04,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,More than 2,200 were\Naboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.02,0:00:34.58,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The paperwork said\Ncompliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:36.36,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The ship said\Notherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.16,0:00:38.53,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Some boats left\Nunderfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.19,0:00:40.23,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The law failed one way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.83,0:00:42.23,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Evacuation failed\Nanother.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.32,0:00:44.41,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Afterward,\Ninvestigators pushed the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.41,0:00:45.50,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,correction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.16,0:00:48.30,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Count people carried,\Nnot tonnage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.35,0:00:51.43,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Two years later, Solis\Nturned that lesson
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.43,0:00:53.51,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,into international\Nrulemaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.38,0:00:56.28,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The old category kept\Nmeasuring yesterday's
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.28,0:00:58.18,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,ship while approving\Ntomorrow's risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.98,0:01:02.35,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Small causes, massive\Nconsequences.
